TITLE: Fireworks injure 17 at Mexico town's Day of Dead celebration
SUMMARY: Officials in Mexico say a fireworks explosion at a Day of the Dead celebration injured 17 people

TITLE: Mexico City autopsy says woman slain, disputing state study
SUMMARY: Mexico City prosecutors say an autopsy on a local woman found dead in the neighboring state of Morelos shows she was killed by blunt force trauma

TITLE: War fallout, aid demands overshadow climate talks in Egypt
SUMMARY: Each year there are high hopes for the two-week United Nations climate gathering and, almost inevitably, disappointment when it doesn’t deliver another landmark pact like the one agreed 2015 in Paris

TITLE: Fire, building collapse injures 20 people in Iraq's capital
SUMMARY: Iraqi authorities say more than two dozen people were injured when a commercial building in the capital caught fire and collapsed

TITLE: Tanzania: Small passenger plane crashes into Lake Victoria
SUMMARY: A plane has crashed into Lake Victoria on approach to an airport in Tanzania

TITLE: Monitors say 6 killed in Syria's shelling of tent settlement
SUMMARY: First responders and opposition war monitors say Syrian government forces have shelled tent settlements housing families displaced by the country’s conflict in the rebel-held northwest, killing at least 10 people and wounding dozens

TITLE: Italy stops 35 migrants from getting off rescue ship in port
SUMMARY: The captain of a charity-operated migrant rescue ship has refused Italian orders to leave a Sicilian port after authorities refused to let 35 migrants disembark

TITLE: Ukraine warns of Russian 'brutality' in eastern region
SUMMARY: The mayor of Kyiv, Ukraine’s capital, is warning residents that they must prepare for the worst this winter if Russia keeps striking the country’s energy infrastructure

TITLE: Nicaragua ruling party seeks to expand hold in local votes
SUMMARY: It's been an electoral campaign without rallies, demonstrations or even real opposition

TITLE: Haiti gang leader to lift fuel blockade amid shortages
SUMMARY: A powerful gang leader says he is lifting a blockade at a key fuel terminal that has strangled Haiti’s capital for nearly two months

TITLE: Pope appeals for Lebanon leaders to put interests aside
SUMMARY: Pope Francis is appealing for Lebanon’s politicians to put their personal interests aside and agree on a path to help the country emerge from years of economic meltdown and a new political vacuum

TITLE: Israel's premier calls for unity after Netanyahu victory
SUMMARY: Israel’s outgoing prime minister has issued a plea for national unity, days after he was defeated in national elections by the former premier, Benjamin Netanyahu

TITLE: World in crisis a grim backdrop for UN climate talks
SUMMARY: Envoys from around the globe gathered Sunday in the Egyptian seaside resort of Sharm el-Sheikh for talks on tackling climate change amid a multitude of competing crises

TITLE: Cameroonian President Paul Biya marks 40 years in power
SUMMARY: President Paul Biya of Cameroon is marking 40 years in power but staying out of the spotlight as questions swirl around the 89-year-old leader

TITLE: Official: 3 dead, 32 hurt in bus accident in northern Turkey
SUMMARY: Turkey’s health minister says three people have been killed in a bus accident in northern Turkey

TITLE: Japan PM vows to strengthen military at int'l naval review
SUMMARY: Japan’s Prime Minister Fumio Kishida says his country urgently needs to strengthen its military capabilities as security risks increase including threats from North Korea and Russia’s war on Ukraine

TITLE: Amnesty: Egypt has days to save jailed activist's life
SUMMARY: The head of Amnesty International says that the proceedings of COP27 will be stained by the death of Egypt's leading rights activist on a hunger and water strike in prison if Egyptian authorities do not release him within days

TITLE: Ex-PM Khan says march on Pakistani capital to resume Tuesday
SUMMARY: Former Pakistani prime minister Imran Khan says a protest march toward the capital Islamabad suspended after he was wounded by a gun shot in an apparent attempt on his life will resume Tuesday

TITLE: Ethnic Serbs rally in Kosovo after leaving jobs in protest
SUMMARY: Several thousand ethnic Serbs have rallied in Kosovo as a dispute over vehicle license plates heightened ongoing tensions between Serbia and its former province

TITLE: Ukraine warns of Russian 'brutality' in eastern region
SUMMARY: Ukrainian authorities say Russian forces are stepping up their strikes in a fiercely contested region of eastern Ukraine

TITLE: Pope in Bahrain: Treatment of prisoners a measure of society
SUMMARY: Pope Francis wrapped up the first-ever papal trip to Bahrain by encouraging priests and nuns to keep ministering to the Gulf kingdom’s tiny Catholic flock

TITLE: Bus bomb kills 1, wounds 10 others in southern Philippines
SUMMARY: Philippine officials say a homemade bomb has exploded in a bus in a southern city and killed one passenger and wounded 10 others in an attack they suspect may be part of an extortion attempt

TITLE: Tens of thousands ride bikes on typically busy Dubai highway
SUMMARY: For a few brief hours, the skyscraper-lined superhighway that cuts through the center of Dubai emptied of the cars always clogging it to give way to tens of thousands of bicyclists

TITLE: Japan PM vows to strengthen military at int'l naval review
SUMMARY: Japan’s Prime Minister Fumio Kishida says his country urgently needs to strengthen its military capabilities amid a worsening security environment in the East and South China seas and threats from North Korea and Russia's war on Ukraine
